==English==

===Etymology===
Named after the council of Nicea in 325, called by the emperor Constantine, to settle the question of the nature of Christ.

===Noun===
'''Nicene Creed'''
#The [[orthodox]] [[creed]] setting out the Catholic church's position on the [[Holy Trinity]] quoted below.
